title.narrative: 2016 World Food Programme WFP Prepositioned Funds

description.narrative: The World Food Programme (WFP) is Australia's largest humanitarian partner and one of the highest performing multilateral agencies funded by Australia. WFP plays a critical role in the international response to crises through the provision of food assistance, cash and voucher transfers, nutrition interventions and logistics and telecommunications support. WFP also works to strengthen the resilience of developing communities through food security and disaster preparedness programs. Funding under this investment supports WFP's emergency operations in priority countries identified by Australia. The total value of this multi-country initiative is $43 million, to be expensed by WFP during the 2016-17 financial year.
